## API Test Classification

### 1. True No-Mock HTTP

- Primary evidence: [API_tests/setup_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/API_tests/setup_test.go), [integration/integration_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/integration/integration_test.go), and [e2e_tests/setup_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/e2e_tests/setup_test.go)
- Why this qualifies:
  - real Gin engine bootstrapped
  - requests sent through `ServeHTTP`
  - real repositories and services wired
  - live PostgreSQL pool required via `DATABASE_URL`
  - no DI overrides or mocked providers in the main API/e2e harness
- Files:
  - `API_tests/*.go`
  - `integration/integration_test.go`
  - `e2e_tests/*.go`

### 2. HTTP With Mocking

- [internal/handler/customer_update_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/customer_update_test.go)
  - `TestCustomerHandler_Update_NameOnlyPreservesEncryptedFields`
  - `TestCustomerHandler_Update_ExplicitEmptyStringClearsField`
  - HTTP request goes through Gin, but repo and encryption service are test doubles.
- [internal/handler/report_validation_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/report_validation_test.go)
  - `TestReportHandler_Create_RejectsUnsupportedReportType`
  - `TestReportHandler_Create_AcceptsSupportedReportTypes`
  - repo is a stub.
- [internal/handler/coverage_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/coverage_test.go)
  - `TestDownloadExport_AuditorDeniedForSensitive`
  - `TestPostRestoreBackup_HappyPath`
  - `TestPostRestoreBackup_ServiceError_RedirectsWithError`
  - uses `sensitiveReportRepo` and `stubBackupService`.
- [internal/handler/auditor_masking_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/auditor_masking_test.go)
  - page handler requests with stub fulfillment/tier/customer/shipping repos.

