## Mock Detection

### What is mocked or stubbed

- `recordingCustomerRepo`, `identityEncryptionSvc`
  - where: [internal/handler/customer_update_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/customer_update_test.go)
  - effect: request reaches handler, but persistence and crypto are replaced
- `stubReportRepo`
  - where: [internal/handler/report_validation_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/report_validation_test.go)
  - effect: HTTP handler tested with fake export repository
- `sensitiveReportRepo`, `stubBackupService`
  - where: [internal/handler/coverage_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/coverage_test.go)
  - effect: page/report and restore handlers tested against stubs
- `stubFulfillRepo`, `stubTierRepo`, `stubCustRepo2`, `stubTimelineRepo`, `stubShippingRepo`, `stubExceptionRepo`
  - where: [internal/handler/auditor_masking_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/handler/auditor_masking_test.go)
  - effect: page handler HTTP tests bypass real repositories
- Extensive service-level stubs such as `stubUserRepo`, `stubTierRepo`, `stubReservationRepo`, `stubSendLogRepo`, `stubNotificationRepo`, `stubReportRepo`, `stubFulfillmentRepo`
  - where: [internal/service/additional_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/service/additional_test.go), [internal/service/fixes_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/service/fixes_test.go), [internal/service/messaging_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/service/messaging_test.go), [internal/service/coverage_extra_test.go](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/internal/service/coverage_extra_test.go)
  - effect: unit tests only, not valid no-mock API coverage
- Frontend spies/stubs
  - where: [static/js/app.test.js](/Users/yosef/Documents/Projects/TASK-req_7dee0d28cda9/repo/static/js/app.test.js)
  - evidence: `vi.stubGlobal`, `vi.spyOn(...).mockImplementation(...)`
  - effect: valid frontend unit testing, but still mocked browser globals

### What was not found

- No `jest.mock`
- No `vi.mock`
- No `sinon.stub`
- No NestJS-style `overrideProvider` / `overrideGuard`

## Coverage Summary

- Total counted endpoints: **64**
- Endpoints with HTTP tests: **64**
- Endpoints with true no-mock HTTP tests: **64**
- HTTP coverage: **100%**
- True API coverage: **100%**

Strict caveat:

- This 100% figure applies only to the API endpoint inventory above.
- It does **not** mean all server-rendered page routes are covered.
- It does **not** mean the tests are uniformly deep. Several endpoints are exercised only through shallow success/status checks or only through one branch.

